.TH il-dis 1 "Viper" "viper-il-dis" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
il-dis \- lower textual IL to Viper bytecode and print the decoded listing
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B il-dis
[\fIoptions\fR] \fIFILE.il\fR
.SH DESCRIPTION
\fBil-dis\fR parses a textual Viper IL module, lowers it to Viper bytecode,
and prints the decoded bytecode listing to stdout, including the constant,
global, and native pools.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB--raw\fR
Include raw 32-bit instruction words alongside the decoded listing.
.TP
\fB--no-pools\fR
Omit the constant/global/native pool listings.
.TP
\fB--version\fR
Show the IL version and exit.
.TP
\fB-h\fR, \fB--help\fR
Show command help and exit.
.SH EXIT STATUS
0 on success; non-zero on argument, I/O, parse, or lowering failure.
.SH SEE ALSO
\fBviper\fR(1), \fBil-verify\fR(1), \fBilrun\fR(1)
